1
00:00:01,510 --> 00:00:04,947
I left that room
and sat in this one

2
00:00:04,972 --> 00:00:06,302
And this was a
corridor from here

3
00:00:06,327 --> 00:00:09,687
Anyone who wanted to pray or
go to the bathroom

4
00:00:10,339 --> 00:00:11,875
I met someone here

5
00:00:13,854 --> 00:00:15,859
He said, If you
need anything

6
00:00:15,884 --> 00:00:19,427
I said to him,
Why are you asking that?

7
00:00:19,818 --> 00:00:22,708
He said, I will
be released today

8
00:00:24,349 --> 00:00:28,021
I said, I want you to go to
my family and tell them I am fine

9
00:00:28,046 --> 00:00:30,807
And that I am here and, God willing,
I will be released, and things like that

10
00:00:32,057 --> 00:00:34,688
After that I went back and
moved to the first room

11
00:00:36,641 --> 00:00:39,740
After that I went back and
moved to the first room

12
00:00:40,182 --> 00:00:42,917
The ones they brought in and the
ones they disappeared, I saw them

13
00:00:43,938 --> 00:00:46,568
And those who came from
ISIS were masked

14
00:00:47,688 --> 00:00:51,464
At 9 or 10 at night,
we had to be asleep

15
00:00:51,489 --> 00:00:52,870
They did not allow any
sound after that

16
00:00:58,469 --> 00:01:02,037
Interviewer: When you were inside this room,
what sounds did you hear from outside?

17
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:03,782
And what did the
place smell like?

18
00:01:04,537 --> 00:01:06,438
We heard whoever
was being flogged

19
00:01:07,219 --> 00:01:09,172
And someone screaming and
saying, I will not do it again

20
00:01:09,511 --> 00:01:11,438
Just this time, by God
I will not do it again

21
00:01:12,375 --> 00:01:13,730
We used to hear
different things

22
00:01:23,964 --> 00:01:26,594
Interviewer: About the people who
were with you inside this room

23
00:01:27,532 --> 00:01:29,355
Did you make
friends with them?

24
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:32,092
Or only that person who would
deliver a message to your family?

25
00:01:32,117 --> 00:01:34,592
No, only that person, because I did
not like to build relationships here

26
00:01:34,617 --> 00:01:38,160
Interviewer: Those who were inside
this cell, what were their charges?

27
00:01:38,185 --> 00:01:40,321
Did you know them, and were any
of them your neighbors in the area?

28
00:01:40,556 --> 00:01:42,561
Only one person. He was
one of my neighbors

29
00:01:43,134 --> 00:01:44,905
And he is now with
the security forces

30
00:01:45,295 --> 00:01:47,951
They also detained him
because of cigarettes

31
00:01:49,748 --> 00:01:50,998
They also flogged him
and released him

32
00:01:51,962 --> 00:01:54,306
Interviewer: Is there an unforgettable
incident that happened to you in this room?

33
00:01:54,331 --> 00:01:56,363
Tell us about it now

34
00:01:56,388 --> 00:01:58,837
What happened, and
what made you leave?

35
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:04,879
It was prayer time and we
got up for ablution to pray

36
00:02:04,904 --> 00:02:06,597
I went out from
here and heard sounds

37
00:02:07,196 --> 00:02:08,967
And there was
metal here

38
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:12,893
A piece of metal

39
00:02:13,338 --> 00:02:16,463
And there was a small
hole, so I looked through it

40
00:02:16,775 --> 00:02:18,859
A person was standing here
in the middle of the courtyard

41
00:02:18,884 --> 00:02:22,114
Holding a sword and
holding it like that

42
00:02:23,130 --> 00:02:24,562
And he was masked

43
00:02:27,557 --> 00:02:30,213
Interviewer: What did you feel
when you saw that scene?

44
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:34,301
I do not know what to tell you.
I was young, of course I felt afraid
